name: IPoser
description:
v1.5

这是一个使用unity开发的人物姿势图片生成工具，可以独立运行，并生成png格式姿势图。

再次重申：可以在运行时手动调整窗口分辨率了，只需要用鼠标拖拉窗口边缘即可。

更新内容：

1.加入了打开程序时就可以选择分辨率功能

2.移除了通过滑块调整角度

3.加入了Gizmo功能，可以直接点击肢体显示出Gizmo，再旋转Gizmo调整肢体角度

(一个小更新：修正了上面3中的一个小BUG)

机翻：


To restate again: The window resolution can be manually adjusted at runtime by simply dragging the edges of the window with the mouse.

1. Added the feature to select resolution when opening the program.

2. Removed the function to adjust angles using a slider.

3. Added the Gizmo function, which allows users to click on limbs to display the Gizmo, and then rotate the Gizmo to adjust limb angles.

(A small update: a minor bug in the third item above has been fixed.)

v1.3

这是一个使用unity开发的人物姿势图片生成工具，可以独立运行，并生成png格式姿势图。

基本操作说明：

1.界面：

•左下角的"Screen Shot"，是截屏功能，调整好姿势和视角后，可以点击这个按钮截图，截图目录在 IPoserV1.3\IPoser V1.3_Data

•右下角的"Reset"，是人体所有组件角度复位功能

•右上角的面板，用于调整被选取的人体组件角度，具体操作是鼠标左键点选组件后，面板上会显示组件名称和角度，这时就可以直接拖动滑块调整了。

2.鼠标操作：

•左键点击人体，可以选取人体组件

•右键按住移动鼠标，可以旋转镜头角度

•(如果有中间滚轮），转动滚轮，可以缩放画面

•(如果有中键或中间滚轮可以被按下）,按下后，移动鼠标可以移动镜头中心点位置

机翻英文：

This is a tool for generating character posture images developed using Unity. It can run independently and generate PNG format posture images. Basic operation instructions:

1. Interface:

- The "Screen Shot" button in the bottom left corner is the screen capture function. After adjusting the posture and viewing angle, you can click this button to take a screenshot. The screenshot directory is in "IPoserV1.3\IPoser V1.3_Data".

- The "Reset" button in the bottom right corner is the function to reset the angles of all body components.

- The panel in the top right corner is used to adjust the angle of the selected body component. The specific operation is to left-click on the component and then the panel will display the component name and angle, which can be adjusted directly by dragging the slider.

2. Mouse operation:

- Left-click on the body to select the body component. - Right-click and move the mouse to rotate the camera angle.

- (If there is a middle scroll wheel), rotate the scroll wheel to zoom the image.

- (If there is a middle button or middle scroll wheel that can be pressed), pressing it and then moving the mouse can move the camera center point position.
